Okay... So I noticed Franks now has a A from the health department. With that being said now was the perfect time to try a pie. When I called my order I asked that it be "Well Done" , it wasn't. I always do this from every pizza place I order from. The delivery person came to bring (in 30 minutes) my pie very fast. The total was $15.75 , I asked the driver if he had change for a $20? I was thinking of getting a $1 back and giving him the rest. Funny thing, he didn't have change. I have heard that this is a ploy that some delivery guys do to get a bigger tip. Maybe so? But next time I'll be sure to have exact change or put it on my debit card.  As for the pizza, it was VERY UNDERCOOKED and doughy as you can see from the pic . But it  did has a good taste.  Frank's could have made this a 5 star review. All they had to do was 1. Made sure the delivery guy had change. 2. Make the pie like the customer asked.  Maybe next time?

Frank's Pizza is so much more than pizza.  There is also a full line of salads, pasta dishes, second course entrees and desserts.  The chef is very creative.  He dreams up a new dish or pizza every day.  And he also creates a warm environment for friends and family.
Both in the restaurant and from delivery, the service is prompt and friendly.  The food is good, cooked well and very tasty.  The portions are generous, but not excessive.

Serves a wide variety of pizzas.  The "spincione" (traditional Sicilian, soft-bread pizza) is particularly popular, as are the fresh mozzarella pizza and the pesto pizza.  On their more creative days, they might also make a pizza with fresh fruit.  Their entrees are great too.  Save room for dessert.  The cannoli are fantastic.
